    <Aside type="note" header="Note" mdxType="Aside">
      <p>{`You can use filters to drill down and examine the data at a granular level. Filters include client country, client device type, client IP, client request host, client request URI, client request user agent, edge response status, origin IP, and origin response status.`}</p>
    </Aside>
    <p>{`Each panel has a set of filters that are applied to the results for that panel only, as shown in the following example. Click the funnel icon in the top panel menu bar to display a list of panel-specific filters.`}</p>
    <p>{`The default time interval is set to 24 hours. Note that for correct filter calculations, you need to exclude Worker subrequests (`}<strong parentName="p">{`WorkerSubrequest`}</strong>{` = `}<em parentName="p">{`false`}</em>{`) and purge requests (`}<strong parentName="p">{`ClientRequestMethod`}</strong>{` is not `}<em parentName="p">{`PURGE`}</em>{`).`}</p>
